eracity%20of%20the%20recordings%2C%20in%20which%20Alito%20%E2%80%94%20who%20recently%20came%20under%20fire%20over%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-justice-alito-blames-wife-pro-trump-symbol-flag-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupside-down%20American%20flag%3C%2Fa%3E%20seen%20outside%20his%20home%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20seemed%20to%20endorse%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20US%20should%20return%20to%20being%20a%20country%20of%20%26quot%3Bgodliness%26quot%3B%20while%20casting%20doubt%20on%20the%20possibility%20of%20future%20compromise%20between%20liberals%20and%20conservatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20side%20or%20the%20other%20is%20going%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20Alito%20told%20Windsor%20at%20the%20event%2C%20according%20to%20both%20outlets.%20%26quot%3BThere%20can%20be%20a%20way%20of%20working%2C%20a%20way%20of%20living%20together%20peacefully%2C%20but%20it's%20difficult%2C%20you%20know%2C%20because%20there%20are%20differences%20on%20fundamental%20things%20that%20really%20can't%20be%20compromised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWindsor%2C%20who%20has%20made%20a%20career%20of%20documenting%20left-wing%20movements%20like%20Occupy%20Wall%20Street%20and%20targeting%20conservatives%20with%20the%20website%20Project%20Veritas%20Exposed%2C%20continued%20to%20coax%20Alito%2C%20according%20to%20the%20audio%2C%20telling%20the%20justice%20she%20believed%20the%20solution%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bwinning%20the%20moral%20argument.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%2C%20people%20in%20this%20country%20who%20believe%20in%20God%20have%20got%20to%20keep%20fighting%20for%20that%2C%20to%20return%20our%20country%20to%20a%20place%20of%20godliness%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20can%20be%20heard%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20agree%20with%20you%2C%20I%20agree%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Alito%20concurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Roberts'%20remarks%20appeared%20more%20measured.%20He%20rebutted%20Windsor's%20argument%20that%20the%20court%20should%20lead%20the%20country%20morally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWould%20you%20want%20me%20to%20be%20in%20charge%20of%20putting%20the%20nation%20on%20a%20more%20moral%20path%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20chief%20justice%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20reports.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20for%20people%20we%20elect.%20That's%20not%20for%20lawyers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWindsor%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20making%20the%20secret%20recordings%20was%20the%20only%20way%20she%20believed%20she%20could%20get%20answers%20to%20her%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20get%20them%20on%20the%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BSo%20recording%20them%20was%20the%20only%20way%20to%20have%20proof%20of%20that%20encounter.%20Otherwise%2C%20it's%20just%20my%20word%20against%20theirs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250fb2554-9d34-47bd-83ff-b313dbc34284%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20recordings%20could%20backfire%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Adler%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20law%20professor%20at%20Case%20Western%20Reserve%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Windsor's%20recordings%20do%20not%20provide%20any%20new%20insight%20into%20how%20the%20justices%20interpret%20law.%20Instead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20they%20are%20an%20unhelpful%20distraction%20from%20significant%20issues%20facing%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20sort%20of%20thing%20is%20going%20to%20mean%20that%20the%20justices%20do%20things%20%E2%80%94%20like%20go%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Historical%20Society%20or%20equivalent%2C%20other%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0less%20often%2C%26quot%3B%20Adler%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20encourage%20the%20justices%20being%20more%20cloistered%20and%20more%20walled%20off%20from%20citizens%2C%20the%20legal%20community%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20And%20it's%20not%20clear%20why%20that%20would%20be%20good%20for%20the%20country%20or%20for%20the%20court%20or%20anything%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20what%20the%20justices%20said%20on%20tape%2C%20Adler%20said%2C%20can%20be%20gleaned%20from%20public%20speeches%20or%20their%20previous%20case%20rulings%2C%C2%A0which%20Adler%20noted%20are%20much%20more%20thoughtfully%20considered%20than%20spontaneous%20remarks%20made%20in%20response%20to%20a%20stranger%20trying%20to%20provoke%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20tapes%20now%20distract%20from%20the%20serious%20cases%20before%20the%20court%20about%20the%20scope%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-rules-trump-eligibility-campaign-president-colorado-super-tuesday-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejudicial%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-case-january-6-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresidential%20immunity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20issues%20like%20parental%20rights%2C%20gender%20identity%2C%20and%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it'd%20be%20much%2C%20much%20more%20fruitful%20if%20we%20were%20devoting%20time%20to%20helping%20people%20unpack%20and%20understand%20those%20questions%20and%20those%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20because%20that's%20what%20matters%2C%26quot%3B%20Adler%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20Justice%20Alito%20thinks%20that%20the%20country's%20political%20or%20tribal%20divisions%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20solved%20anytime%20soon%20doesn't%20tell%20us%20very%20much.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falito-disqualified-over-flag-incidents-in-lower-court-expert-says-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F